      "acceptanceCriteria": "Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2 used under ISO 9001-registered QMS; software validation records on file at DePuy Synthes and FDA.",
      "rationale": "The FEA solver (Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2) is operated under a documented quality management system. Installation qualification and operational qualification records confirm the executable matches the validated release. Achieved level equals required level for Medium model risk."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Benchmark problems from NAFEMS and ASME V&V 10 suite solved; residuals match analytic solutions within 0.5%.",
      "rationale": "Standard NAFEMS linear-elastic benchmark problems (LE1, LE3, LE10) were solved with the production mesh settings. All residuals fell within 0.5% of analytic solutions, confirming correct code implementation for the element types used in the pedicle screw model."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation GCI < 5% for all three QoIs on three systematically refined meshes.",
      "rationale": "Three mesh refinement levels (coarse 1.2 mm, medium 0.8 mm, fine 0.5 mm element size at screw-rod interface) were evaluated. Grid Convergence Index computed via Richardson extrapolation yielded GCI values of 2.1%, 1.8%, and 3.4% for stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm respectively, all below the 5% threshold."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Nonlinear force-displacement residual norm < 1e-4 at each load step; energy criterion also satisfied.",
      "rationale": "The implicit nonlinear solver converged with normalized residual norms below 1e-5 at every load step across all 11 simulated constructs. Energy convergence criterion was simultaneously satisfied. No divergence events were recorded. Achieved level exceeds required level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of model setup by a second analyst not involved in original construction; checklist-based verification of boundary conditions and material assignments.",
      "rationale": "A second licensed engineer independently reviewed the Ansys project file, confirming correct application of ASTM F1717 fixture boundary conditions, titanium alloy material properties (Ti-6Al-4V per ASTM F136), and load application direction. No use errors were identified."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum isotropic linear-elastic model with contact interfaces justified by literature and prior FDA validation studies; geometric nonlinearity enabled for large-displacement regime.",
      "rationale": "The pedicle screw and rod are modeled as continuum solid bodies with Ti-6Al-4V isotropic elastic properties. Frictional contact (mu=0.2) is applied at screw-rod and rod-fixture interfaces, consistent with published FDA FEA guidance. Geometric nonlinearity is active. This model form has been validated in multiple prior ASTM F1717 studies and is appropriate for the COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from ASTM F136 certificate of conformance; geometry from calibrated CMM measurements; torque-preload relationship from manufacturer torque-tension data.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus (114 GPa) and yield strength (795 MPa) are taken from certificate of conformance for the specific Ti-6Al-4V lot used in testing. Screw and rod geometry was measured by CMM with traceable calibration. Set-screw preload was derived from manufacturer torque-tension data at 4 Nm assembly torque. Uncertainty in material properties is bounded at ±3%."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N=11 constructs from production lots; dimensional inspection confirms conformance to drawing; two independent laboratories.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were assembled from production-representative hardware lots. All constructs passed incoming dimensional inspection per drawing tolerances. Testing was split across two independent laboratories (Lab A n=6, Lab B n=5) to assess inter-laboratory variability. Sample size is sufficient for the Medium model risk level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Multiple load levels or construct configurations tested to characterize response space; at least two distinct test conditions.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under a single load configuration (ASTM F1717 standard fixture, axial compression-bending at 5 degrees). While this configuration is the regulatory standard, only one test condition was evaluated, which does not fully characterize the model response space. Achieved level (1) is below the required level (2); this shortcoming is acknowledged and accepted given the regulatory context of the COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA model inputs (geometry, material, boundary conditions, assembly torque) directly traceable to as-tested construct records; any deviations documented and bounded.",
      "rationale": "Each of the 11 simulated constructs was parameterized using the as-measured CMM dimensions and the specific lot material certificate for that construct. Assembly torque was set to the mean measured value (4.0 ± 0.1 Nm) from the test records. No unresolved discrepancies between simulation inputs and test conditions were identified."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative metric E/uval < 1.96 and percent difference < 10% for all three QoIs; statistical comparison accounts for experimental uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "For all three QoIs (stiffness: 3.2% difference, E/uval=0.87; yield force: 5.1% difference, E/uval=1.12; force at 40 mm: 7.8% difference, E/uval=1.54), the acceptance criteria are satisfied. The validation metric E/uval incorporates experimental measurement uncertainty (load cell calibration, displacement transducer) and model prediction uncertainty. All values fall within the pre-established bounds."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) are directly linked to the COU decision criteria and regulatory submission requirements.",
      "rationale": "The three QoIs are those specified in ASTM F1717 and referenced in FDA guidance for spinal implant submissions. Construct stiffness characterizes elastic behavior; yield force identifies onset of permanent deformation; force at 40 mm represents the ultimate functional limit. All three are directly relevant to the COU decision of demonstrating adequate mechanical performance."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments replicate the COU geometry, loading, and material; any differences between validation and COU scenarios are documented and their impact bounded.",
      "rationale": "The validation constructs use the same non-cannulated 7.5 mm screw geometry, same Ti-6Al-4V alloy, and the same ASTM F1717 test fixture as would be used in regulatory submission testing. The validation activity directly represents the COU scenario. No extrapolation beyond the validated geometry or load regime is required for the COU decision."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level for Medium model risk. The single shortcoming (Test conditions, achieved level 1 vs. required level 2) is accepted given that the ASTM F1717 single-condition protocol is the regulatory standard and additional conditions would not alter the submission decision. All three QoIs satisfy the pre-established quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96 and percent difference < 10%). The credibility package is assessed as sufficient to support a Medium assurance level conclusion.",
